Caracas’ Subway Fare to Double Next Month, El-Troudi Says

-- B y   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 
2011-05-25T14:35:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/caracas-subway-fare-to-double-next-month-el-troudi-says.html
Subway fares in  Venezuela ’s capital
will double to 1 bolivar (23 cents) on June 1 and then rise to
1.5 bolivars on Dec. 1, Caracas Subway President Haiman El- Troudi said.  The added revenue from the fare increase will pay for
maintenance of the system, El-Troudi said in remarks on state
television. No additional fare increases are planned, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Orozco in Caracas at 
 jorozco8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 